{meta: title Just Across the Bridge of Gold}
{meta: artist Hank Snow}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]As the twilight shadows deepen
[G7]Where the weeping willow waves
[C]All alone in tears I'm [F]kneeling
[G7]O'er my sweetheart's lonely [C]grave
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
I regret those words I've spoken
[G7]Every yesterday of tears
[C]That I caused you little [F]darling
[G7]As we wandered through the [C]years
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
I am asking God's forgiveness
[G7]For you're waiting there I know
[C]Out beyond that blue [F]horizon
[G7]Just across the bridge of [C]gold
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
If I'd only read your letter
[G7]Saying you were in despair
[C]That your weary heart was [F]broken
[G7]And in pain was lying [C]there
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
I tonight would not be weeping
[G7]O'er the roses on your grave
[C]But instead dear I'd be [F]happy
[G7]All this sorrow I'd have [C]saved
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
If I only would have listened
[G7]When you told me not to stray
[C]But I said I loved [F]another
[G7]Left you there and went [C]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Now my life is sad and lonely
[G7]Down life's path I trudge along
[C]But I'll meet you up in [F]heaven
[G7]When from this old world I've [C]gone
{end_of_verse}

